<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-07-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-07-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="462" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.12/1198: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morrow</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-07-17T14:00:00-04:00">July 17, 1930—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>182. Department’s 176, July 11, 1 p.m.,<note n="28" xml:id="d462fn28"><hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_543">p.
                                543</ref>.</note> and your 148, July 16, 4 p.m. You are authorized
                            to initiate concurrent yet independent negotiations when you consider it
                            expedient to do so for (1) an en bloc settlement of claims and (2) Rio
                            Grande rectification with related questions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>